     2â†’title: Loop Control
     3â†’description: Control agent execution with built-in loop management using stopWhen and prepareStep
     4â†’---
     5â†’
     6â†’# Loop Control
     7â†’
     8â†’You can control both the execution flow and the settings at each step of the agent loop. The loop continues until:
     9â†’
    10â†’- A finish reasoning other than tool-calls is returned, or
    11â†’- A tool that is invoked does not have an execute function, or
    12â†’- A tool call needs approval, or
    13â†’- A stop condition is met
    14â†’
    15â†’The AI SDK provides built-in loop control through two parameters: `stopWhen` for defining stopping conditions and `prepareStep` for modifying settings (model, tools, messages, and more) between steps.
    16â†’
    17â†’## Stop Conditions
    18â†’
    19â†’The `stopWhen` parameter controls when to stop execution when there are tool results in the last step. By default, agents stop after 20 steps using `stepCountIs(20)`.
    20â†’
    21â†’When you provide `stopWhen`, the agent continues executing after tool calls until a stopping condition is met. When the condition is an array, execution stops when any of the conditions are met.
    22â†’
    23â†’### Use Built-in Conditions
    24â†’
    25â†’The AI SDK provides several built-in stopping conditions:
    26â†’
    27â†’```ts
    28â†’import { ToolLoopAgent, stepCountIs } from 'ai';
    29â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
    30â†’
    31â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
    32â†’  model: __MODEL__,
    33â†’  tools: {
    34â†’    // your tools
    35â†’  },
    36â†’  stopWhen: stepCountIs(20), // Default state: stop after 20 steps maximum
    37â†’});
    38â†’
    39â†’const result = await agent.generate({
    40â†’  prompt: 'Analyze this dataset and create a summary report',
    41â†’});
    42â†’```
    43â†’
    44â†’### Combine Multiple Conditions
    45â†’
    46â†’Combine multiple stopping conditions. The loop stops when it meets any condition:
    47â†’
    48â†’```ts
    49â†’import { ToolLoopAgent, stepCountIs, hasToolCall } from 'ai';
    50â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
    51â†’
    52â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
    53â†’  model: __MODEL__,
    54â†’  tools: {
    55â†’    // your tools
    56â†’  },
    57â†’  stopWhen: [
    58â†’    stepCountIs(20), // Maximum 20 steps
    59â†’    hasToolCall('someTool'), // Stop after calling 'someTool'
    60â†’  ],
    61â†’});
    62â†’
    63â†’const result = await agent.generate({
    64â†’  prompt: 'Research and analyze the topic',
    65â†’});
    66â†’```
    67â†’
    68â†’### Create Custom Conditions
    69â†’
    70â†’Build custom stopping conditions for specific requirements:
    71â†’
    72â†’```ts
    73â†’import { ToolLoopAgent, StopCondition, ToolSet } from 'ai';
    74â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
    75â†’
    76â†’const tools = {
    77â†’  // your tools
    78â†’} satisfies ToolSet;
    79â†’
    80â†’const hasAnswer: StopCondition<typeof tools> = ({ steps }) => {
    81â†’  // Stop when the model generates text containing "ANSWER:"
    82â†’  return steps.some(step => step.text?.includes('ANSWER:')) ?? false;
    83â†’};
    84â†’
    85â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
    86â†’  model: __MODEL__,
    87â†’  tools,
    88â†’  stopWhen: hasAnswer,
    89â†’});
    90â†’
    91â†’const result = await agent.generate({
    92â†’  prompt: 'Find the answer and respond with "ANSWER: [your answer]"',
    93â†’});
    94â†’```
    95â†’
    96â†’Custom conditions receive step information across all steps:
    97â†’
    98â†’```ts
    99â†’const budgetExceeded: StopCondition<typeof tools> = ({ steps }) => {
   100â†’  const totalUsage = steps.reduce(
   101â†’    (acc, step) => ({
   102â†’      inputTokens: acc.inputTokens + (step.usage?.inputTokens ?? 0),
   103â†’      outputTokens: acc.outputTokens + (step.usage?.outputTokens ?? 0),
   104â†’    }),
   105â†’    { inputTokens: 0, outputTokens: 0 },
   106â†’  );
   107â†’
   108â†’  const costEstimate =
   109â†’    (totalUsage.inputTokens * 0.01 + totalUsage.outputTokens * 0.03) / 1000;
   110â†’  return costEstimate > 0.5; // Stop if cost exceeds $0.50
   111â†’};
   112â†’```
   113â†’
   114â†’## Prepare Step
   115â†’
   116â†’The `prepareStep` callback runs before each step in the loop and defaults to the initial settings if you don't return any changes. Use it to modify settings, manage context, or implement dynamic behavior based on execution history.
   117â†’
   118â†’### Dynamic Model Selection
   119â†’
   120â†’Switch models based on step requirements:
   121â†’
   122â†’```ts
   123â†’import { ToolLoopAgent } from 'ai';
   124â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
   125â†’
   126â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
   127â†’  model: 'openai/gpt-4o-mini', // Default model
   128â†’  tools: {
   129â†’    // your tools
   130â†’  },
   131â†’  prepareStep: async ({ stepNumber, messages }) => {
   132â†’    // Use a stronger model for complex reasoning after initial steps
   133â†’    if (stepNumber > 2 && messages.length > 10) {
   134â†’      return {
   135â†’        model: __MODEL__,
   136â†’      };
   137â†’    }
   138â†’    // Continue with default settings
   139â†’    return {};
   140â†’  },
   141â†’});
   142â†’
   143â†’const result = await agent.generate({
   144â†’  prompt: '...',
   145â†’});
   146â†’```
   147â†’
   148â†’### Context Management
   149â†’
   150â†’Manage growing conversation history in long-running loops:
   151â†’
   152â†’```ts
   153â†’import { ToolLoopAgent } from 'ai';
   154â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
   155â†’
   156â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
   157â†’  model: __MODEL__,
   158â†’  tools: {
   159â†’    // your tools
   160â†’  },
   161â†’  prepareStep: async ({ messages }) => {
   162â†’    // Keep only recent messages to stay within context limits
   163â†’    if (messages.length > 20) {
   164â†’      return {
   165â†’        messages: [
   166â†’          messages[0], // Keep system instructions
   167â†’          ...messages.slice(-10), // Keep last 10 messages
   168â†’        ],
   169â†’      };
   170â†’    }
   171â†’    return {};
   172â†’  },
   173â†’});
   174â†’
   175â†’const result = await agent.generate({
   176â†’  prompt: '...',
   177â†’});
   178â†’```
   179â†’
   180â†’### Tool Selection
   181â†’
   182â†’Control which tools are available at each step:
   183â†’
   184â†’```ts
   185â†’import { ToolLoopAgent } from 'ai';
   186â†’__PROVIDER_IMPORT__;
   187â†’
   188â†’const agent = new ToolLoopAgent({
